{"article_id":"MU48y3AyIZIO2san","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"Story highlights","depth":2},{"id":1,"text":"Democratic groups say","depth":3},{"id":2,"text":"they contacted nearly 750,000 voters over the weekend","depth":3},{"id":3,"text":"The recall fight stems from a battle over collective bargaining rights for public employees","depth":5},{"id":4,"text":"Republican Gov . Scott Walker faces off against Democrat Tom Barrett , mayor of Milwaukee","depth":5},{"id":5,"text":"In the canon of political cliches , `` it all comes down to turnout '' is among the most tired .","depth":8},{"id":6,"text":"But in the case of the polarizing and closely watched Wisconsin recall election , the maxim happens to ring true .","depth":8},{"id":7,"text":"Public polling , internal polling and campaign strategists all tell the same story :","depth":9},{"id":8,"text":"Republican Gov . Scott Walker is clinging to a tiny lead over his Democratic opponent , Milwaukee Mayor Tom Barrett ,","depth":12},{"id":9,"text":"heading into Tuesday 's vote .","depth":12},{"id":10,"text":"And the number of undecided voters has dwindled to almost zero ,","depth":12},{"id":11,"text":"strategists in both parties say ,","depth":12},{"id":12,"text":"meaning that the only mission","depth":12},{"id":13,"text":"left for both sides","depth":12},{"id":14,"text":"is to get their rabid supporters to the polls .","depth":11},{"id":15,"text":"`` Our sole focus right now is on our grassroots get-out-the-vote-effort , ''","depth":9},{"id":16,"text":"said Ben Sparks , a spokesman for the Wisconsin Republican Party .","depth":9},{"id":17,"text":"JUST WATCHED","depth":9},{"id":18,"text":"Wisconsin recall :","depth":11},{"id":19,"text":"Dry run for November ?","depth":11},{"id":20,"text":"Replay More Videos ...","depth":10},{"id":21,"text":"MUST WATCH","depth":11},{"id":22,"text":"Wisconsin recall :","depth":12},{"id":23,"text":"Dry run for November ?","depth":12},{"id":24,"text":"04:23","depth":10},{"id":25,"text":"JUST WATCHED","depth":11},{"id":26,"text":"Wisconsin teachers duel over recall","depth":12},{"id":27,"text":"Replay More Videos ...","depth":12},{"id":28,"text":"MUST WATCH","depth":11},{"id":29,"text":"Wisconsin teachers duel over recall","depth":12},{"id":30,"text":"02:39","depth":12},{"id":31,"text":"JUST WATCHED","depth":10},{"id":32,"text":"Politics gone wild in Wisconsin","depth":12},{"id":33,"text":"Replay More Videos ...","depth":12},{"id":34,"text":"MUST WATCH","depth":12},{"id":35,"text":"Politics gone wild in Wisconsin","depth":13},{"id":36,"text":"02:50","depth":13},{"id":37,"text":"JUST WATCHED","depth":9},{"id":38,"text":"Check out CNN 's new electoral map","depth":11},{"id":39,"text":"Replay More Videos ...","depth":11},{"id":40,"text":"MUST WATCH","depth":11},{"id":41,"text":"Check out CNN 's new electoral map","depth":13},{"id":42,"text":"02:09 `` We Are Wisconsin , '' an umbrella group","depth":14},{"id":43,"text":"funded by labor unions and the Democratic Governors Association ,","depth":14},{"id":44,"text":"said","depth":12},{"id":45,"text":"it contacted nearly 750,000 voters over the weekend , with the goal","depth":10},{"id":46,"text":"of touching 1.4 million people with phone calls or door knocks by the close of polls Tuesday .","depth":10},{"id":47,"text":"Meanwhile , the state GOP and the Republican National Committee ,","depth":8},{"id":48,"text":"which are coordinating some of their efforts with the Walker campaign ,","depth":8},{"id":49,"text":"boasted Monday","depth":7},{"id":50,"text":"that they have identified and contacted 4 million voters since January","depth":7},{"id":51,"text":"-- a number","depth":8},{"id":52,"text":"that has national Republicans speculating","depth":9},{"id":53,"text":"that they can put the state in play for Mitt Romney in November .","depth":9},{"id":54,"text":"The recall fight has its roots in Walker 's successful push in early 2011","depth":7},{"id":55,"text":"to strip public employees of their collective bargaining rights in an effort","depth":8},{"id":56,"text":"to close an ugly budget shortfall .","depth":8},{"id":57,"text":"The push sparked a bitter partisan battle between Walker and Democrats in the state legislature ,","depth":7},{"id":58,"text":"and set off a wave of historic protests from union members inside and outside the state capitol in Madison .","depth":7},{"id":59,"text":"After Walker signed the controversial budget bill in March 2011 ,","depth":7},{"id":60,"text":"labor organizers subsequently managed to collect 900,000 certified signatures","depth":8},{"id":61,"text":"to trigger a recall","depth":8},{"id":62,"text":"and are now among those","depth":7},{"id":63,"text":"leading the final get-out-the-vote push .","depth":7},{"id":64,"text":"On Monday , at a Madison-area branch of the American Federation of State , County and Municipal Employees","depth":7},{"id":65,"text":"( AFSCME ) ,","depth":7},{"id":66,"text":"Barrett supporters spent the day","depth":7},{"id":67,"text":"popping in","depth":8},{"id":68,"text":"to pick up fliers for door-to-door voter contact efforts .","depth":8},{"id":69,"text":"Randy Case , a retiree from Cross Plains , was among those","depth":7},{"id":70,"text":"who dropped by the AFSCME office","depth":8},{"id":71,"text":"to help .","depth":8},{"id":72,"text":"He said","depth":8},{"id":73,"text":"Walker deserves to be removed from office","depth":9},{"id":74,"text":"because he trampled on Wisconsin 's cherished tradition of fair play in state government .","depth":9},{"id":75,"text":"`` This is a friendly state , ''","depth":9},{"id":76,"text":"Case said .","depth":9},{"id":77,"text":"`` People get along here ,","depth":10},{"id":78,"text":"and I think","depth":12},{"id":79,"text":"in our government , that has meant we elect people","depth":13},{"id":80,"text":"who work across the aisle","depth":14},{"id":81,"text":"and listen to other side .","depth":14},{"id":82,"text":"And that has just been absent with this current administration .","depth":11},{"id":83,"text":"It 's 'my way or the highway , '","depth":11},{"id":84,"text":"which is simply not a Wisconsin value .","depth":11},{"id":85,"text":"It 's not how we govern ourselves . ''","depth":10},{"id":86,"text":"JUST WATCHED","depth":6},{"id":87,"text":"White House weighs in on Wisconsin","depth":6},{"id":88,"text":"Replay More Videos ...","depth":6},{"id":89,"text":"MUST WATCH","depth":7},{"id":90,"text":"White House weighs in on Wisconsin","depth":7},{"id":91,"text":"00:45","depth":5},{"id":92,"text":"JUST WATCHED","depth":8},{"id":93,"text":"Wisconsin recall workers face hostility","depth":8},{"id":94,"text":"Replay More Videos ...","depth":8},{"id":95,"text":"MUST WATCH","depth":9},{"id":96,"text":"Wisconsin recall workers face hostility","depth":9},{"id":97,"text":"02:02","depth":9},{"id":98,"text":"JUST WATCHED","depth":11},{"id":99,"text":"Conservatives rally for Scott Walker","depth":11},{"id":100,"text":"Replay More Videos ...","depth":11},{"id":101,"text":"MUST WATCH","depth":12},{"id":102,"text":"Conservatives rally for Scott Walker","depth":12},{"id":103,"text":"03:20","depth":9},{"id":104,"text":"JUST WATCHED","depth":11},{"id":105,"text":"Barrett downplays lack of natl . support","depth":11},{"id":106,"text":"Replay More Videos ...","depth":13},{"id":107,"text":"MUST WATCH","depth":13},{"id":108,"text":"Barrett downplays lack of natl . support","depth":12},{"id":109,"text":"03:18","depth":11},{"id":110,"text":"Walker argues","depth":10},{"id":111,"text":"that his reforms are working ,","depth":10},{"id":112,"text":"pointing to a projected budget surplus and a modest uptick in jobs","depth":10},{"id":113,"text":"since he took office last year .","depth":10},{"id":114,"text":"Democrats have tried to poke holes in those numbers ,","depth":10},{"id":115,"text":"but according to recent poll from Marquette University Law School ,","depth":11},{"id":116,"text":"a slight majority of voters approve of Walker 's performance in Madison .","depth":11},{"id":117,"text":"The Milwaukee Journal Sentinel , Barrett 's hometown paper , also came to Walker 's defense with a helpful messaging point last week ,","depth":10},{"id":118,"text":"writing in an editorial","depth":11},{"id":119,"text":"that the governor deserves to finish his term .","depth":11},{"id":120,"text":"Walker is not the only Republican","depth":8},{"id":121,"text":"facing a recall Tuesday .","depth":8},{"id":122,"text":"Lt. Gov . Rebecca Kleefisch is on the ballot against Democrat Mahlon Mitchell , a Fitchburg firefighter","depth":8},{"id":123,"text":"dubbed `` M & M '' by some of his supporters .","depth":8},{"id":124,"text":"The undercard also features four of the Republican state senators","depth":7},{"id":125,"text":"who helped Walker pass his budget reforms .","depth":7},{"id":126,"text":"Just one GOP loss in those recall races would flip control of the state Senate back to Democrats , at least until the next election in November .","depth":7},{"id":127,"text":"But the marquee race is between Walker and Barrett , a rematch of the 2010 governor 's race .","depth":8},{"id":128,"text":"In that historically Republican year , Walker edged Barrett in their original matchup by 5 points .","depth":8},{"id":129,"text":"Different dynamics are at work on Tuesday , though ,","depth":10},{"id":130,"text":"giving Democrats some hope","depth":11},{"id":131,"text":"even though Walker is considered the narrow favorite .","depth":11},{"id":132,"text":"While the anti-Walker fervor may have waned","depth":11},{"id":133,"text":"since protests consumed the state capitol grounds in early 2011 ,","depth":11},{"id":134,"text":"insiders here predict","depth":11},{"id":135,"text":"that turnout on both sides is likely to be higher","depth":12},{"id":136,"text":"than it was for the original Walker-Barrett race .","depth":12},{"id":137,"text":"But even in the race 's eleventh hour , strategists in both parties are struggling to figure out","depth":9},{"id":138,"text":"whether turnout will be closer to 2008 levels ,","depth":11},{"id":139,"text":"when nearly 70 % of eligible Wisconsin voters participated in the presidential election ,","depth":11},{"id":140,"text":"or 2010 ,","depth":11},{"id":141,"text":"when voter turnout dropped to 49 % .","depth":11},{"id":142,"text":"Democrats are hoping for the 2008 model .","depth":11},{"id":143,"text":"Almost 3 million people voted in that election ,","depth":12},{"id":144,"text":"and the state went heavily for Barack Obama .","depth":12},{"id":145,"text":"`` It was a low turnout in 2010 and a high turnout in 2008 , ''","depth":12},{"id":146,"text":"said former Wisconsin Sen. Russ Feingold ,","depth":13},{"id":147,"text":"who spent Monday traveling the state","depth":14},{"id":148,"text":"rallying Democrats .","depth":14},{"id":149,"text":"`` If we get anywhere near 2008 or even halfway there ,","depth":13},{"id":150,"text":"we are going to win ,","depth":13},{"id":151,"text":"because those folks are more likely to vote for Tom Barrett . ''","depth":12},{"id":152,"text":"But unlike 2008 ,","depth":12},{"id":153,"text":"when Republican turnout underwhelmed ,","depth":12},{"id":154,"text":"Wisconsin voters on both sides are now engaged at a level","depth":12},{"id":155,"text":"not seen in recent memory .","depth":12},{"id":156,"text":"`` We have an example of Hatfields and McCoys","depth":13},{"id":157,"text":"going on in this state","depth":14},{"id":158,"text":"like we have never seen , ''","depth":14},{"id":159,"text":"said Brian Nemoir , a Milwaukee-based Republican strategist .","depth":12},{"id":160,"text":"`` People are hyper-engaged , as much in support for their own candidate as in disgust for the opponent . ''","depth":11},{"id":161,"text":"Handmade signs are nearly as prevalent as official ones .","depth":10},{"id":162,"text":"Some locals say","depth":12},{"id":163,"text":"they have resorted to lowering their voices in public","depth":14},{"id":164,"text":"when discussing the recall","depth":14},{"id":165,"text":"to avoid setting off arguments with strangers .","depth":13},{"id":166,"text":"The Marquette University poll revealed","depth":13},{"id":167,"text":"that 26 % of all voters have slapped a bumper sticker on their car","depth":14},{"id":168,"text":"or planted a sign in their lawn .","depth":14},{"id":169,"text":"The same survey found","depth":13},{"id":170,"text":"that a third of voters have simply stopped talking politics with someone","depth":15},{"id":171,"text":"they know","depth":15},{"id":172,"text":"because the race is so heated .","depth":14},{"id":173,"text":"And this is all in a state with a historical reputation for collegiality and Midwestern politeness .","depth":9},{"id":174,"text":"A flood of campaign money , much of it from out-of-state interest groups","depth":8},{"id":175,"text":"and most of it benefiting Republicans ,","depth":8},{"id":176,"text":"is partially responsible for the hothouse political climate .","depth":7},{"id":177,"text":"About $ 64 million has been spent on the race since November 2011 ,","depth":9},{"id":178,"text":"an analysis from the Center for Public Integrity found .","depth":9},{"id":179,"text":"That 's a new state record ,","depth":9},{"id":180,"text":"shattering the previous record of $ 37.4 million","depth":10},{"id":181,"text":"spent during the 2010 governor 's race .","depth":10},{"id":182,"text":"Beginning last fall ,","depth":9},{"id":183,"text":"Walker seized on a loophole in Wisconsin law","depth":10},{"id":184,"text":"that allows incumbents in recall elections to raise unlimited sums .","depth":10},{"id":185,"text":"Walker outraised his opponent by an almost 8-1 margin ,","depth":10},{"id":186,"text":"collecting $ 30.5 million to Barrett 's $ 4 million .","depth":10},{"id":187,"text":"Roughly two-thirds of Walker 's contributions came from out of state ,","depth":11},{"id":188,"text":"the Center for Public Integrity reported ,","depth":11},{"id":189,"text":"while only a quarter of Barrett 's funds originated from outside Wisconsin .","depth":10},{"id":190,"text":"Beyond the individual campaigns , independent groups have played a major role in the race ,","depth":8},{"id":191,"text":"helping saturate television and radio airwaves with negative advertising .","depth":8},{"id":192,"text":"The Republican Governors Association , for instance , has spent more than $ 8 million on Walker 's behalf , most it on television ads .","depth":7},{"id":193,"text":"Working against Walker are unions like AFSCME , the American Federation of Teachers , the National Education Association and the Service Employees International Union ,","depth":7},{"id":194,"text":"which have also steered millions of dollars to the state in their efforts","depth":8},{"id":195,"text":"to unseat the governor .","depth":8}],"relations":[{"parent":391,"left":198,"right":390,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":198,"left":0,"right":197,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":197,"left":1,"right":2,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":390,"left":280,"right":389,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":280,"left":248,"right":279,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":248,"left":199,"right":247,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":199,"left":3,"right":4,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":247,"left":240,"right":246,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":240,"left":210,"right":239,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":210,"left":200,"right":209,"relation":"explanation","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":200,"left":5,"right":6,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":209,"left":207,"right":208,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":207,"left":7,"right":206,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":206,"left":203,"right":205,"relation":"causal","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":203,"left":201,"right":202,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":2